A savings and investment platform, PiggyVest paid out over N242billion to over 3.5million customers in 2021; its Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Somto Ifezue has disclosed. Ifezue in a newsletter disclosed the plan of the platform to do better with its products, services and opportunities in 2022. Launched in 2016 as primarily a savings app, Piggyvest, formerly known as Piggy Bank helps and businesses and individuals including students manage their finances effectively – save and invest with ease. “For the past five and a half years, we have been committed to building a product that truly benefits our customers. It’s not been an easy task making sure everyone is happy, but we are grateful for the opportunity, and we never take it for granted,” he said. On what to expect from PiggyVest in 2022; Ifezue asked customers to expect overhauling of the app to make it more user-friendly and secured; adding more features to help customers in their financial journey would be introduced. “We are bringing loads of investment opportunities for you via ‘Investify’, which is PiggyVest’s way of helping subscribers grow their wealth. We will also ensure better and faster customer support this year” he assured.